<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-XbtmoHPY-IQkq_KSk85Zjw" name="measurement_requirements,_WAwy0P1IEd20w98rSqT2fg" guid="-XbtmoHPY-IQkq_KSk85Zjw" changeDate="2009-04-02T13:46:38.749-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To clarify and document the Business Objectives and Operational Objectives&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To document the Business and Operational Measures&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To document a list of prioritized practices&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To document the practice metrics&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To document the measurement infrastructure requirements&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To document the measurement process requirements&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>This is a critical&amp;nbsp;artifact and without it the measures being gathered would have no context.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>This individual artifact could be combined with the Measurement Requirements, Measurement Specifications and the&#xD;
Measurement Process Model into a Measurement Plan.</reasonsForNotNeeding>
  <briefOutline>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Business Objectives&lt;/strong> - a list of the relevant business objectives with a brief explanation of why&#xD;
        each is important&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Business Measures&lt;/strong> - a brief description of the business measures.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Operational Objectives&lt;/strong> - a list of operational objectives that support the Business Objectives&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Operational Measures&lt;/strong> - the measures that give proof to the Operational Objectives are described&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Prioritized Practices&lt;/strong> - a list of the practices that are required to be implemented to achieve the&#xD;
        Operational objectives.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Define Practice Metrics&lt;/strong> - measures defined for each of the practices&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Value Traceability Tree&lt;/strong> - Business objectives are traced to operational objectives and then to&#xD;
        practices.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Measurement Infrastructure Requirements&lt;/strong> - requirements for the Measurement Infrastructure are&#xD;
        identified, (i.e. Rational Insight will be used the data collection and reporting environment).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Measurement Process Requirements&lt;/strong> - requirements related to the entire measurement process are&#xD;
        detailed, (i.e. stakeholders, vision, high level use cases).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></briefOutline>
  <representationOptions>This information is normally captured in a word processing document, but it could also be maintained in a Requirement&#xD;
Management tool.</representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
